   <div class="main">
      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp01_039" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 1.39</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> चतुराशीतिपीठेषु <mark>सिद्धमेव सदाभ्यसेत्</mark> ।</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>द्वासप्तति</mark><mark>सहस्रेषु</mark> <mark>सुषुम्णा</mark><mark>मिव नाडिषु</mark> ॥</p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> caturāśītipīṭheṣu <mark>siddham eva sadābhyaset</mark> /</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>dvāsaptati</mark><mark>sahasreṣu</mark> <mark>suṣumṇā</mark><mark>m iva nāḍiṣu</mark> //</p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> From among the eighty-four postures, one should regularly practise just <i>siddhāsana</i>, in the same way from among the 72,000 channels [one should practise, focusing on]
               <i>suṣumṇā</i>. </div>
            <details class="philcomm-d">
               <summary>Philological Commentary</summary>
               <div class="philcomm"> It is odd to have <i>suṣumṇām</i> as the object of the verb <i>abhyaset</i>. This reading is well attested by manuscripts of the <i>Haṭhapradīpikā</i> and is also found in the <i>Yogacintāmaṇi</i>, which attributes it to the <i>Yogasāramañjarī</i>. Perhaps, the second hemistich was added somewhat haphazardly by Svātmārāma, and
                  then others have tried to make sense of it by changing <i>suṣumnām iva nāḍiṣu</i> to <i>nāḍīnāṃ malaśodhanam</i>, which occurs in the <i>Jyotsnā</i> (1.39). The reading <i>nāḍīnāṃ malaśodhanam/e</i> is probably a patch as no other texts say that <i>siddhāsana</i> clears the channels. However, the idea of purifying the channels can be found in
                  other contexts (e.g., <i>Kumbhakapaddhati</i> 120) and may hark back to an earlier notion of flushing (<i>cālana</i>) the channels (e.g., <i>Amṛtasiddhi</i> 11.6).</div>
            </details>
         </div>
         <div class="crit">
            <div class="apparatus">
               <h3>Readings</h3>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">siddham eva sadābhyaset</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] siddhāsanaṃ sadābhyaset (<span class="siglum" title="δ1 Sampurnananda Library Sarasvati Bhavan 30069">δ<sub>1</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="δ3 Lalchand M-6494">δ<sub>3</sub></span>), abhyaset siddhāsanaṃ sadā (<span class="siglum" title="δ2 Privat collection">δ<sub>2</sub></span>)</div>
