   <div class="altrec">
      <div class="main">
         <div class="hpmeta">
            <div class="text">
               <div id="hp01_055_4" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 1.55*4</span><div class="versdev">
                     <p class="hpvers"> श्रुति<mark>प्रतीतिः</mark> स्वगुरुप्रतीतिः </p>
                     <p class="hpvers"> स्वात्मप्रतीतिर्मनसो<mark>ऽपि रोधः</mark> । </p>
                     <p class="hpvers"> एतानि सर्वाणि <mark>समुच्चितानि</mark> </p>
                     <p class="hpvers"> मतानि धीरैरिह साधनानि ॥ <span class="inlineref">(<span class="siglum" title="Δ V19,K3,C7">Δ</span>)</span>
                        </p>
                     </div>
                  <div class="versltn">
                     <p class="hpvers"> śruti<mark>pratītiḥ</mark> svagurupratītiḥ </p>
                     <p class="hpvers"> svātmapratītir manaso<mark>’pi rodhaḥ</mark> / </p>
                     <p class="hpvers"> etāni sarvāṇi <mark>samuccitāni</mark> </p>
                     <p class="hpvers"> matāni dhīrair iha sādhanāni // <span class="inlineref">(<span class="siglum" title="Δ V19,K3,C7">Δ</span>)</span>
                        </p>
                     </div>
               </div>
               <div class="translation"> Realisation from scripture, realisation from one’s own guru, realisation from oneself
                  and the cessation of mind; all these methods have been combined and taught by the
                  wise in this tradition.</div>
               <details class="philcomm-d">
                  <summary>Philological Commentary</summary>
                  <div class="philcomm"> Verse 1.55.4 is in some of the δ manuscripts and is quoted in <i>Yogacintāmaṇi</i> with attribution to the <i>Haṭhapradīpikā</i>. The reading in the <i>Yogacintāmaṇi</i> `cessation of mind’ (<i>manonirodhaḥ</i>) is better than <i>manaso ’pi bodhaḥ</i> (the δ reading) in a yogic context. </div>
               </details>
            </div>
            <div class="crit">
               <div class="metre">
                  	      Metre:  Upajāti </div>
               <div class="apparatus">
                  <h3>Readings</h3>
                  <div class="app altrec"><span class="lem">pratītiḥ</span> (<span class="siglum" title="δ2 Privat collection">δ<sub>2</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="δ3 Lalchand M-6494">δ<sub>3</sub></span>) ] prītaḥ (<span class="siglum" title="δ1 Sampurnananda Library Sarasvati Bhavan 30069">δ<sub>1</sub></span>)</div>
                  <div class="app altrec"><span class="lem">’pi rodhaḥ</span><span class="siglum" title="emendation"> (em.)</span> ] ’pi bodhaḥ (<span class="siglum" title="Δ V19,K3,C7">Δ</span>)</div>
                  <div class="app altrec"><span class="lem">samuccitāni</span> (<span class="siglum" title="δ1 Sampurnananda Library Sarasvati Bhavan 30069">δ<sub>1</sub></span>) ] samuddhṛtāni (<span class="siglum" title="δ2 Privat collection">δ<sub>2</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="δ3 Lalchand M-6494">δ<sub>3</sub></span>)</div>
               </div>
               <details class="testimonia-d">
                  <summary>Testimonia</summary>
                  <div class="testimonia"> <i>Yogacintāmaṇi</i> f. 48v 
                     <div class="lg">
                        <p class="versinnote">haṭhapradīpikāyām--</p>
                        <p class="versinnote">śrutipratītiś ca gurupratītiḥ svātmapratītiś ca manonirodhaḥ |</p>
                        <p class="versinnote">etāni sarvāṇi samuccitāni matāni dhīrair iha sādhanāni ||</p> 
