   <div class="main">
      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp02_028" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 2.28</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> धात्विन्द्रिया<mark>न्तःकरण</mark><mark>प्रसादं</mark></p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> दद्याच्च <mark>कान्तिं</mark> दहन<mark>प्रदीप्तिम्</mark> ।</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> अशेष<mark>दोषोपचयं</mark> निहन्या-</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>दभ्यस्य</mark>मानं <mark>जल</mark>बस्ति<mark>कर्म</mark> ॥</p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> dhātvindriyā<mark>ntaḥkaraṇa</mark><mark>prasādaṃ</mark></p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> dadyāc ca <mark>kāntiṃ</mark> dahana<mark>pradīptim</mark> /</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> aśeṣa<mark>doṣopacayaṃ</mark> nihanyād</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>abhyasya</mark>mānaṃ <mark>jala</mark>basti<mark>karma</mark> //</p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> When practised repeatedly, the water enema (<i>jalabasti</i>) technique bestows clarity of the bodily constituents, senses and mind, radiance,
               [and] stimulation of the digestive fire, and removes [excessive] accumulation of all
               humours. </div>
         </div>
         <div class="crit">
            <div class="metre">
               	      Metre:  Upajāti </div>
            <div class="apparatus">
               <h3>Readings</h3>
