   <div class="main">
      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp02_040" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 2.40</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> यावद्बद्धो मरुद्देहे <mark>यावच्चित्तं</mark> <mark>निराश्रयम्</mark> ।</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>याव</mark><mark>द्वीक्षा</mark> भ्रुवो<mark>र्मध्ये</mark> ताव<mark>त्काल</mark>भयं कुतः ॥<span class="fn" title="ε3 adds here: bahvāmayo pi nāpnoti pavanābhyāsatatparaḥ / samanaskontakabhayaṃ tasmāt pavanam abhyaset //. Cf. ."><b>*</b></span>
                     </p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> yāvad baddho marud dehe <mark>yāvac cittaṃ</mark> <mark>nirāśrayam</mark> /</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>yāva</mark><mark>d vīkṣā</mark> bhruvo<mark>r madhye</mark> tāva<mark>t kāla</mark>bhayaṃ kutaḥ //<span class="fn" title="ε3 adds here: bahvāmayo pi nāpnoti pavanābhyāsatatparaḥ / samanaskontakabhayaṃ tasmāt pavanam abhyaset //. Cf. ."><b>*</b></span>
                     </p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> So long as the breath is bound in the body, so long as the mind is without support,
               so long as the gaze is on the middle of the brow, where is the fear of death? </div>
            <details class="philcomm-d">
               <summary>Philological Commentary</summary>
               <div class="philcomm"> We have adopted the reading <i>vīkṣā</i> in the third verse quarter, which is an emendation of α1 and α2’s <i>vīkṣed</i>. The verb <i>vīkṣed</i> is likely an error as the <i>yāvat</i> clauses appear to have been written as nominal phrases. The reading <i>vīkṣā</i> occurs in the same verse of the six-chapter version of the <i>Vivekamārtaṇḍa</i> (siglum T), which sometimes preserves old readings of that text. </div>
            </details>
         </div>
         <div class="crit">
            <div class="apparatus">
               <h3>Readings</h3>
