      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp03_002" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 3.2</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> सुप्ता गुरुप्रसादेन <mark>यदा जागर्ति कुण्डली</mark> ।</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>तदा</mark> <mark>सर्वाणि पद्मानि</mark> भिद्यन्ते ग्रन्थयोऽपि च ॥</p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> suptā guruprasādena <mark>yadā jāgarti kuṇḍalī</mark> /</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>tadā</mark> <mark>sarvāṇi padmāni</mark> bhidyante granthayo’pi ca //</p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> When the sleeping <i>kuṇḍalinī</i> awakens through the favour of the guru, then all the lotuses are pierced, and the
               knots too, [dots ] </div>
            <details class="philcomm-d">
               <summary>Philological Commentary</summary>
               <div class="philcomm"> The usual meaning of <i>jāgarti</i> would be “is wakeful” rather than “awakens”, which explains the variant <i>bodhitā</i>. </div>
            </details>
         </div>
