                  <div class="versltn">
                     <p class="hpvers"> vajrolī <mark>tv amarolī</mark> ca <mark>sahajolī</mark> tridhā <mark>matāḥ</mark> / </p>
                     <p class="hpvers"> <mark>eteṣāṃ</mark> lakṣaṇaṃ <mark>vakṣye</mark> kartavyaṃ ca viśeṣataḥ // <span class="inlineref">(<span class="siglum" title="β2 Lalchand M-2089">β<sub>2</sub></span>, <span class="siglum" title="βω Sampurnananda Library Sarasvati Bhavan 29899">β<sub>ω</sub></span> and <span class="siglum" title="η2 MSPP Jodhpur 2230 η2ac η2pc">η<sub>2</sub></span>)</span>
                        </p> 
                     </div>
               </div>
               <div class="translation"> [With] <i>Amarolī</i> and <i>Sahajolī</i>, Vajrolī is considered to be threefold. I shall teach their characteristics and the
                  details of how they should be performed. </div>
