   <div class="main">
      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp03_038" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 3.38</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>चित्तं</mark> <mark>चरति खे</mark> <mark>यस्मा</mark>ज् जिह्वा चरति खे <mark>गता</mark> ।</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>तेनैषा</mark> खेचरी <mark>नाम</mark> <mark>मुद्रा</mark> <mark>सिद्धैर्नमस्कृता</mark> ॥ 
                     </p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>cittaṃ</mark> <mark>carati khe</mark> <mark>yasmā</mark>j jihvā carati khe <mark>gatā</mark> /</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>tenaiṣā</mark> khecarī <mark>nāma</mark> <mark>mudrā</mark> <mark>siddhair namaskṛtā</mark> // 
                     </p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> Because the mind moves (<i>carati</i>) in the ether (<i>khe</i>) and the tongue moves (<i>carati</i>) in the cavity (<i>khe</i>), this mudrā is called <i>khecarī</i> [and] is worshipped by the Siddhas. </div>
         </div>
         <div class="crit">
            <div class="apparatus">
               <h3>Readings</h3>
