   <div class="main">
      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp03_048" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 3.48</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>चुम्बन्ती</mark> यदि <mark>लम्बिकाग्रम्</mark> अनिशं जिह्वा <mark>रस</mark>स्यन्दिनी</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>सक्षारा</mark> <mark>कटुकाथ</mark> <mark>दुग्ध</mark><mark>सदृशी</mark> <mark>मध्वाज्य</mark><mark>तुल्या</mark><mark>थवा</mark> । </p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> व्याधीनां हरणं <mark>जरान्तकरणं</mark> <mark>शास्त्रागमोदीरणं</mark> </p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>तस्य स्या</mark>द<mark>मरत्व</mark>मष्ट<mark>गुणव</mark><mark>त्सिद्धाङ्गना</mark><mark>कर्षणम्</mark> ॥</p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>cumbantī</mark> yadi <mark>lambikāgram</mark> aniśaṃ jihvā <mark>rasa</mark>syandinī</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>sakṣārā</mark> <mark>kaṭukātha</mark> <mark>dugdha</mark><mark>sadṛśī</mark> <mark>madhvājya</mark><mark>tulyā</mark><mark>thavā</mark> / </p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> vyādhīnāṃ haraṇaṃ <mark>jarāntakaraṇaṃ</mark> <mark>śāstrāgamodīraṇaṃ</mark> </p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>tasya syā</mark>d a<mark>maratva</mark>m aṣṭa<mark>guṇava</mark><mark>t siddhāṅganā</mark><mark>karṣaṇam</mark> //</p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> If the tongue, while oozing nectar and constantly kissing the tip of the uvula, is
               salty, pungent, like milk or the same as honey and ghee, diseases are eliminated for
               [the yogi], old age is stopped, he can recite treatises and scriptures, attains immortality
               together with the eightfold powers, and attracts Siddha women. </div>
         </div>
         <div class="crit">
            <div class="metre">
               	      Metre:  Śārdūlavikrīḍita </div>
            <div class="apparatus">
               <h3>Readings</h3>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">cumbantī</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] vipitīṃ (<span class="siglum" title="γ1 NGMPP G 25-2 γ1ac γ1pc">γ<sub>1</sub></span>)</div>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">lambikāgram</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] laṃbakārgram (<span class="siglum" title="β1">β<sub>1</sub></span>), lampikāgram (<span class="siglum" title="δ2 Privat collection">δ<sub>2</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="δ3 Lalchand M-6494">δ<sub>3</sub></span>)</div>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">rasa</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] śiraḥ (<span class="siglum" title="βω Sampurnananda Library Sarasvati Bhavan 29899">β<sub>ω</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="η2 MSPP Jodhpur 2230 η2ac η2pc">η<sub>2</sub></span>)</div>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">sakṣārā</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] sākṣārā (<span class="siglum" title="α1 NGMPP B 62-20 α1ac α1pc">α<sub>1</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="δ1 Sampurnananda Library Sarasvati Bhavan 30069">δ<sub>1</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="ε2 NGMPP E-1528-1 / E-1527-7(4)">ε<sub>2</sub></span>), sakṣāra (<span class="siglum" title="η2 MSPP Jodhpur 2230 η2ac η2pc">η<sub>2</sub></span>), sakṣīro° (<span class="siglum" title="β1">β<sub>1</sub></span>)</div>
