   <div class="main">
      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp03_049" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 3.49</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>एकं</mark> <mark>सृष्टि</mark><mark>मयं</mark> बीजं एका मुद्रा <mark>च</mark> खेचरी ।</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> एको <mark>देवो</mark> <mark>निरालम्ब</mark> <mark>एका</mark><mark>वस्था</mark> मनोन्मनी ॥ 
                     </p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> <mark>ekaṃ</mark> <mark>sṛṣṭi</mark><mark>mayaṃ</mark> bījaṃ ekā mudrā <mark>ca</mark> khecarī /</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> eko <mark>devo</mark> <mark>nirālamba</mark> <mark>ekā</mark><mark>vasthā</mark> manonmanī // 
                     </p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> There is one seed [syllable], which contains creation, one <i>mudrā</i>, <i>khecarī</i>, one god, the unsupported, and one state, beyond mind. </div>
         </div>
         <div class="crit">
            <div class="apparatus">
               <h3>Readings</h3>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">ekaṃ</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] eka (<span class="siglum" title="δ3 Lalchand M-6494">δ<sub>3</sub></span>), evaṃ (<span class="siglum" title="γ1 NGMPP G 25-2 γ1ac γ1pc">γ<sub>1</sub></span>)</div>
