   <div class="main">
      <div class="hpmeta">
         <div class="text">
            <div id="hp03_054" class="hp"><span class="number">HP 3.54</span><div class="versdev">
                  <p class="hpvers"> अपानप्राण<mark>योरैक्यं</mark> <mark>क्षयो</mark> मूत्रपुरीषयोः ।</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> युवा भवति वृद्धोऽपि सततं मूल<mark>बन्धनात्</mark> ॥<span class="fn" title="γ1 adds the following verse here: bandhamūlaṃ yena tena tena vighnāṃ nivāritaḥ / ajarāmaratāṃ yāti yathā pañcamukho haraḥ //"><b>*</b></span>
                     </p> 
                  </div>
               <div class="versltn">
                  <p class="hpvers"> apānaprāṇa<mark>yor aikyaṃ</mark> <mark>kṣayo</mark> mūtrapurīṣayoḥ /</p>
                  <p class="hpvers"> yuvā bhavati vṛddho’pi satataṃ mūla<mark>bandhanāt</mark> //<span class="fn" title="γ1 adds the following verse here: bandhamūlaṃ yena tena tena vighnāṃ nivāritaḥ / ajarāmaratāṃ yāti yathā pañcamukho haraḥ //"><b>*</b></span>
                     </p> 
                  </div>
            </div>
            <div class="translation"> <i>Prāṇa</i> and <i>apāna</i> unite, urine and faeces diminish, [and] even an old man becomes young as a result
               of the continuous application of the root lock. </div>
            <details class="philcomm-d">
               <summary>Philological Commentary</summary>
               <div class="philcomm"> The diminishing of urine and faeces as a result of success in yoga is mentioned in
                  the <i>Amanaska</i> (1.50c) and <i>Dattātreyayogaśāstra</i> (80a). </div>
            </details>
         </div>
         <div class="crit">
            <div class="apparatus">
               <h3>Readings</h3>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">°yor aikyaṃ</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] °yor aikya (<span class="siglum" title="γ1 NGMPP G 25-2 γ1ac γ1pc">γ<sub>1</sub></span>), °yor aikye (<span class="siglum" title="η2 MSPP Jodhpur 2230 η2ac η2pc">η<sub>2</sub></span>), °yoś caikyaṃ (<span class="siglum" title="δ2 Privat collection">δ<sub>2</sub></span>), °yor aikyāt (<span class="siglum" title="ε4 Jodhpur 23532 ε4i.t. ε4mg. alternative reading written by the first hand in margin or interlinearly (J11)">ε<sub>4</sub></span>)</div>
               <div class="app"><span class="lem">kṣayo</span> (<span class="siglum" title="cett. ceteri">cett.</span>) ] kṣayaṃ (<span class="siglum" title="α3 GOML 18885">α<sub>3</sub></span>), kṣayān (<span class="siglum" title="γ1 NGMPP G 25-2 γ1ac γ1pc">γ<sub>1</sub></span> <span class="siglum" title="ε4 Jodhpur 23532 ε4i.t. ε4mg. alternative reading written by the first hand in margin or interlinearly (J11)">ε<sub>4</sub></span>)</div>
